teleproto3 — per-directory licence manifest
=============================================

This monorepo contains code under multiple licences. Each top-level
directory ships its own LICENSE file which is authoritative for that
directory. This manifest exists to make the split obvious at a glance
(Chromium / Kubernetes convention).

Directory          Licence                           Start point
-----------------  --------------------------------  --------------------
spec/              Apache License, Version 2.0       spec/LICENSE
lib/               Apache License, Version 2.0       lib/LICENSE
conformance/       Apache License, Version 2.0       conformance/LICENSE
server/            MTProxy upstream licence          server/LICENSE
                   (vendored via `git subtree` from
                   github.com/teleproxy/teleproxy
                   — active community upstream, continuation of the
                   archived github.com/TelegramMessenger/MTProxy.
                   Not relicensable without upstream.)

Root-level documentation files (README.md, OWNERSHIP.md, SECURITY.md,
CONTRIBUTING.md, this manifest) are Apache 2.0.

Questions about licensing? Open an issue or see OWNERSHIP.md.
